Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: American Association for the Study of Liver Diseases – AASLD is an organization of scientists and health care professionals committed to preventing and curing liver disease. It has grown to an international society responsible for all aspects of hepatology, and its annual meeting, “The Liver Meeting”, has grown in attendance from 12 to more than 9,500 physicians, surgeons, researchers, and allied health professionals from around the world.  American Association for the Study of Liver Diseases – AASLD sponsors two topical conferences each year in clinical, basic, hepatitis, or pediatric hepatology. Its three journals, including Hepatology, Liver Transplantation, and Clinical Liver Disease provide the latest research findings for hepatology and surgery of the liver. The organization’s membership includes all professionals dedicated to hepatobiliary discoveries and patient care. American Association for the Study of Liver Diseases – AASLD was founded in 1950 by a small group of leading liver specialists to bring together those who had contributed to the field of hepatology. It is headquartered in Alexandria, V.A.

Description: Recharged, rebooted, reborn; Detroit Electric is bringing pure electric excitement to the world, one pin at a time! Also visit us at www.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: It’s hard to imagine that back in the early 1900’s, electric cars were the most prolific vehicle. And guess who helped spark the movement. Our founder, William C Anderson made his first Detroit Electric in 1907. By 1910 we were leading the way, selling up to 2,000 cars a year. Petrol cars were unreliable and dirty, but Detroit Electrics could be charged at home and used in an instant – making them extremely popular. Even Henry Ford’s wife drove one. As the years passed and petrol engines became cheaper and stronger, sales of electric vehicles dropped. Finally, after producing a total of 13,000 cars – a world record for electric vehicles in the 20th century – the last Detroit Electric was shipped in 1939. We’re back, over 70 years on. Back in Detroit and back to reignite positive movement in the motor industry. Just as we did in 1907. Proving that we were never behind the times. We were ahead of it.

Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: I am so excited about this business. Nashville Tn has grown so much in the last few years , hotel after hotel, more music venues for every type of music, it's really becoming one of the top tourists destinations. This city needs a liquor store right downtown by all the hotels and tourist attractions, the closest is about 15-20 min in a cab. Now if you are on vacation who wants to take a taxi to go get drinks and pay while they wait for you to shop, who wants to spend all their money they brought on a few drinks? Not too many, but .. Everyone likes to have a few drinks before they go out to loosen up and relax or the restaurant industry workers, bartenders, servers etc want a drink to take home but by the time they get off work and drive somewhere all the liquor stores are closed. Plus not only is it in high demand the merchandise for Beaver Liquors would be the hottest new thing around, all the tourists would want to take home a shirt, cozie or hat. We all do that when on a vacation, got to have some type of souvenir to take home. I hope you can see the potential in this company and help me bring it to life. I would be more than happy to speak to anyone if there are any questions. Thank you for reading my dream, hopefully it will become a reality!!

Description: Programmable Static Site Hosting
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: BitBalloon is a static site hosting platform that automates performance optimization, deployment and form handling. Whenever a user either drags & drops a site folder onto bitballoon.com (or makes a call to the API) the site is automatically optimized and deployed onto production hosting. Any forms in the HTML of a deployed site will automatically work. BitBalloon is the first hosting platform where this is possible. The form submissions get stored in a database that's accessible from a site dashboard as well as the BitBalloon API. All of BitBalloons features can be controlled through an open OAuth2 based developer API, which makes it possible to extend and leverage the platform in interesting ways. The API is also integrated with Zapier, where BitBalloon form submissions are a trigger service for other API's. It's a flexible way to automate key business functionality related to web form submissions without having to write any code.  BitBalloon operates a reseller model so other software vendors can use BitBalloon to power a static site publishing component in their own products.

Our mission is to provide the most accurate and up to date coverage of the communities in Amador County in its entirety. This is accomplished through our printed newspapers, the Amador Ledger Dispatch and the Mother Lode Life and Times, as well as utilizing the latest technologies available online through our website ledger-dispatch.com, myachome.com, LocalZ mobile app, Facebook, Instagram and many other online resources. The Amador Ledger Dispatch is published every Friday, while the Mother Lode Life and Times is published every Tuesday. Online efforts are a service that we update and manage daily. Good newspapers reflect what is going on in their communities - great newspapers actively involve themselves with the communities they serve to build a stronger future for all of its citizens.
